A traffic officer sustained serious injuries when she was hit by a wheel that came off a caravan at a road block on Thursday afternoon. The officer was part of a roadblock set up on the N4 in Bronkhorstspruit, Kempton Express reported. Athlenda Mathe of Netcare 911 said the Netcare helicopter was dispatched to a scene around 2pm. Reports indicate the woman was hit by a wheel that came off a caravan at the roadblock. Because of the severity of her injuries, she was airlifted to a level 1 trauma facility in Johannesburg. &#8211; Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter. &nbsp; For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.